title: Enamel Decoration and Tinder Cord
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
description: Rectangular, with rounded sides; polychrome enameled decoration of abstracted figures and geometric patterns; in the center a plain, A-framed reserve with engraved initials; a gold colored tinder cord with knot at end is housed in side compartment, attached by hook and chain that may be pulled from knob at top. Flat lid hinged on top. Striker on bottom.
